olive oil
2 radish
1 tomato
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
1 tsp honey
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
¾ cup boiling water

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Thinly slice radish. Roughly
chop tomato.
• Cut deep slices, taking care to not slice all the way through, across chicken
breast in 1cm intervals. In a medium bowl, combine chermoula spice
blend, chicken and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Place chicken on a lined oven tray and top with crumbled cheese (see
ingredients). Drizzle with the honey and olive oil, then roast until cooked
through, 12-16 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• While chicken is roasting, boil the kettle. In a medium heatproof bowl, place
couscous and chicken-style stock powder.
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 1 1/2 cups for 4 people) and stir
to combine. Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes. Fluff up
with a fork and set aside.

• To the couscous, add radish, tomato, salad leaves, a drizzle of red wine
vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine.

• Divide tomato and radish couscous between plates. Top with chermoula and
cheese topped chicken.
• Drizzle Greek-style yoghurt over couscous to serve.